{"build_type":"executable","description":"Parses Alder Lake generation Intel hybrid CPU topology from proc cpuinfo whose path arrives in the request under cpuinfo. Reads a large leading window (procfs blocks are ~1700 bytes each) and walks every processor block recording each core id and its frequency, then classifies each cpu per observation: a core id shared by two cpus is a performance SMT pair, a unique one is an efficiency core. Emits logical_threads and the explicit per-cpu maps performance_cpu_mask and efficiency_cpu_mask (bit i set means cpu i is in that class), directly usable as affinity masks for pinning so cores cannot be confused.","module_name":"parse-alderlake-hybrid-processor-topology","package_name":"parse-alderlake-hybrid-processor-topology","function_definitions":{"parse-alderlake-hybrid-processor-topology":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"maxread","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":65536},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"freqsize","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":8192},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"cidsize","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_ta